            . My husband is a finman and brazier, and we keep a little shop. The prisoner came in - I was very busy washing, and my back was towards the counter; I heard something put into the scale - I moved from my washing-tub, and was wiping my hands, when the witness came in; we have always the scale hanging up - I have known Miller; Berry lives in the neighbourhood - he never sold me any thing before: there is another general-dealer next door.</p>
               <p>Berry's Defence. I was coming home from work, and Miller came to me, and asked me to sell a bit of copper for him; I did not know any harm in it.</p>
